\"wp-block-image alignfull size-large\"><img src=\"http://7star/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/1-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-914\"/><figcaption>CakePHP, Laravel, Codeigniter Certification</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>CakePHP, Laravel, Codeigniter Certification</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>Web Application Framework</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>Web Application Framework or simply “web framework” is a software framework that is designed to support the development of web applications including web services, web resources, and web APIs. Frameworks are, in short, libraries that help you develop your application faster and smarter!<br><br>Pick any one of these two popular Web Application Frameworks for your Specialization Training.</p></blockquote>\n<!-- /wp:quote -->\n\n<!-- wp:button {\"align\":\"left\",\"className\":\"is-style-outline\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-button alignleft is-style-outline\"><a class=\"wp-block-button__link\" href=\"#\">COURSE DETAILS</a></div>\n<!-- /wp:button --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:image {\"align\":\"full\",\"id\":913,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\",\"className\":\"size-full\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image alignfull size-large size-full\"><img src=\"http://7star/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/2-1.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-913\"/><figcaption>WordPress, Joomla, Drupal Certification</figcaption></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3>WordPress, Joomla, Drupal Certification</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":5} -->\n<h5>CMS - Content Management System</h5>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:quote -->\n<blockquote class=\"wp-block-quote\"><p>CMS stands for content management system. CMS is computer software or an application that uses a database 